body: Good Morning Could you please help me take a look what is wrong with my HoneyBee setting? I just started learning HoneyBee by following Chris Mackey's Honeybee Energy Modeling on youtube. When I labeled surfaces as shown in part 3,  I noticed all texts appeared with strange font: [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/0OuNYC5ZE6Wv6hJgsO2609-78rVciF7sIl44SexTyC3SyzF27OudMUdoC4T4ucTdnSgQ6cXRoluIbIE68xjYcqMCfFVYFO0T/Withoutfontwrong.png) I tried to manually set font, but it did not work [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/0OuNYC5ZE6Xru28A3hBC*ItJyySgbXAkbOVJOopnx-qTMoqlvtFFPt1SNhdJZhvnHkju92oaoTSnQR0b7ImuqN04QOcol7*G/Wrong.png) And for some reason, this problem only happened when I was labeling Surfaces. All text display normally when I was labeling Zones [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/0OuNYC5ZE6ViRM6iDWORDFyFJ9b3Kk4FvX29yB7Xk8qo2C-odCmrCFJHvX*Uv*l060NQyGWlCfQhaFhv88nW2BbzxEBCpzeo/Normal.png) I have no idea what is wrong. Could you please help me take a look? All software are up to date. Here is the battery map [](http://api.ning.com:80/files/0OuNYC5ZE6WSC4XXRkViTRLUtSMdTlXId3X9hbO-VaZaHyxJjyqgiq4uuOBAd5GjUN5xQ9bPM7Vte7k*gCXHFoCy92OYuhTe/WrongBattery.png) Thank you very much.
